node.text: Today I'm wearing #PlaidforDad to raise funds for @cancersociety’s groundbreaking prostate cancer research. With 1 in 9 Canadian men expected to be diagnosed with prostate cancer in their lifetime, we all have a reason to go plaid. Join me and post a photo of yourself in plaid with the hashtag #PlaidforDad. For every post, Janssen will make a $5 donation, up to $20,000, to help the Canadian Cancer Society build a world where no one fears prostate cancer. @prostatecancerccs

node.text: During these uncertain times, there's one thing I'm certain of: no one wants to lose a loved one to prostate cancer. That's why I'm proud to be an ambassador for #PlaidforDad Day. On June 18 – the Friday before Father's Day – join me in going #PlaidforDad and raising funds for @ProstateCancerCCS. Together, we can build a world where no one fears prostate cancer. Sign up to participate with your co-workers, family or friends at www.plaidfordad.ca

node.text: Today I'm wearing #PlaidforDad to raise funds for @cancersociety’s groundbreaking prostate cancer research. With 1 in 9 Canadian men expected to be diagnosed with prostate cancer in their lifetime, we all have a reason to go plaid. Join me and post a photo of yourself in plaid with the hashtag #PlaidforDad. For every post, Janssen will make a $5 donation, up to $20,000, to help the Canadian Cancer Society build a world where no one fears prostate cancer. @prostatecancerccs

node.text: During these uncertain times, there's one thing I'm certain of: no one wants to lose a loved one to prostate cancer. That's why I'm proud to be an ambassador for #PlaidforDad Day. On June 18 – the Friday before Father's Day – join me in going #PlaidforDad and raising funds for @ProstateCancerCCS. Together, we can build a world where no one fears prostate cancer. Sign up to participate with your co-workers, family or friends at www.plaidfordad.ca

Attention Everyone! We will be showing an encore performance of "Wil" for 1 day only in honor of Mr. Shakespeare's Birthday, Friday April 23rd. There is still much work to be done to help The Actors Fund and The AF Canada!
Please visit our website and grab your tickets and donate today! @muchadoaboutwil 
https://www.muchadoaboutwil.com/tickets-donations

Cheers and enjoy the show!

node.text: Hey everyone. Thank you so much for helping us reach our current total of $814,361! But the challenge is not over yet! Today is the last day to donate for the #RedBucketMatchUp and we’re just a few bucks away from our goal of 1 million dollars. Huge thanks to everyone who has given so far. And big things to Gilead Sciences who will double every dollar raised. We have till midnight tonight, so if you haven’t given yet, go to BroadwayCares.org/Eric to donate today.
